The paper proposes a framework for policy fusion in robotics, which suggests that it belongs to the Robotics (cs.RO) category. The use of weight functions that can be learned by back-propagation indicates that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. The paper also discusses the use of Lyapunov functions, which are commonly used in control theory, suggesting that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories. Finally, the experiments involve imitation learning and a real-world robot, indicating that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category.
